[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(7) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "He had wrought folly in Israel.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The great anger of Jacob’s sons agrees as completely with the general harshness of their characters as the silence of the father with his habitual thoughtfulness; but it was aroused by a great wrong. The use, however, of the term ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Israel ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to signify the family of Jacob as distinguished from his person belongs to the age of Moses, and is one of the proofs of the arrangement of these records having been his work. In selecting them, and weaving them together into one history, he would add whatever was necessary, and in the latter half of this verse we apparently have one such addition.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Genesis 34:7",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 34:7",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He had wrought folly — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "All sin is folly: but some sinful actions are attended with such circumstances of ignorance and thoughtlessness, and are so inimical to our temporal as well as eternal interests, that they peculiarly merit the name of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "folly. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Shechem’s sin is termed folly ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in Israel, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "according to the language of after-times; for Israel was not yet a people, but a family only.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
